After the dive Giffords blew kisses to the media, waved, and described the experience as 'wonderful' and 'good stuff' to the Today  show. 

Sitting with her husband after the jump, Ms Giffords told the Today show that her skydive had a 'lot of mountains, a lot of sky' and was 'peaceful, so peaceful'.

She said that it reminded her: 'I'm alive'.

Today show host Savannah Guthrie asked Ms Giffords what emotions she had on January 8, the anniversary of the attack, to which she replied 'happy and sad' but that she wanted to 'move on and move ahead'.

