Ms Giffords is now able to make small movements on her right side which was totally paralyzed and is gathering more of her power of speech.

She is still able to sing and gave a rousing rendition of Tomorrow from Annie. She also wants to become fluent in Spanish again and relearn the French horn.

When asked by Guthrie if she would like to return to political office, Ms Giffords said 'a little bit later', saying that although her recovery was slow, she felt 'pretty good, optimistic'.

